<br>
The &quot;fresh-off-the-boat&quot; newbies I've dealt with, and I've dealt with lots, don't ask for platinum.  They ask for information.  &quot;How do I find the bank?&quot; &quot;How do I find a fire beetle eye?&quot; &quot;How do I get better armor?&quot;  One thing seems consistent in these kinds of newbies: their questions start with &quot;HOW DO *I*...&quot;  They don't expect handouts--they generally want to know how to do things for themselves.<br>
<br>
The &quot;newbies&quot; who come begging for &quot;platz&quot; have played before.<br>
<br>
