<br>
Why don't you have /autolog feature on? I clean mine about once a month. If I have something good I keep it to remember. <br>
<br>
And if you did not wish to slander my guild, then why post it instead of emailing me about it? Use common sense when running into problems like this. I expect people to do what they are suppose to do. I could tell you about over forty cases of bad roleplay from many guilds. But when it comes to the point of begging, or cussing, or some idiotic crap like that I contact an officer or the leader either by /tell or emailing them. <br>
<br>
To address the newbie thing. In your handbook you got with the game it tells you about begging. He is not a complete newbie no. But I consider someone who has never been 30+ a newbie in my eyes. <br>
Thats because at 30th and under you have not seen most of the game nor learned as much that is required to be a novice.<br>
Asking for money doesn't take a college degree.<br>
He did in fact lose his corpse and everything on it. Like most folks under 15 for the first time and losing everything seems horriable. We all know better. <br>
He has been informed that begging is not needed in the Council. He had not learned as much as he needed to know of us. This happened very soon in his membership and no one was online to help him at that time. In fact he is still in trial membership with us. <br>
Goodday to you all.<br>
